div1.p:
Cross-examined. Q. It was a very wicked thing of this woman, was it not? A. Yes; I had been accused of stealing before - I had stolen a sovereign from my mother;
John Fulbrook
is here - he was not with me when I sold the first handkerchief; I never took any handkerchiefs but those three - I did sell one to a boy: it was not one of these three - I found that in Grove-street-fields; I never offered to sell a handkerchief to any body else - no one ever refused to buy one of me; I never offered any man a handkerchief for sale.
